🧠 Generative AI with Large Language Models – MOOC Summary
This repository contains key notes, code, and learning artifacts from the “Generative AI with Large Language Models” course. The course provides a solid foundation in building, fine-tuning, and applying large language models (LLMs) for various generative AI tasks using Python and modern ML tools.

📘 Course Overview:
This course explores how large language models like GPT, BERT, and their variants are used to:

Understand and generate human-like text

Fine-tune pre-trained models for custom NLP tasks

Perform text summarization, classification, Q&A, and more

Build applications using Python and transformer libraries

Dive into prompt engineering and model evaluation techniques

🛠️ Skills & Technologies:
Python Programming

Machine Learning

Natural Language Processing (NLP)

Generative AI Techniques

Transformer Architectures (e.g., GPT, BERT)

Prompt Engineering & Evaluation

📁 Repository Includes:
📝 Concept notes and visual explanations

💻 Python notebooks for hands-on labs

✅ Mini-projects and application demos

🧠 Prompt engineering examples

🔍 Model evaluation metrics and techniques

🎯 Objective:
To understand how generative AI systems work, and gain hands-on experience with LLMs using Python—enabling the creation of intelligent text-based applications and custom NLP solutions.

